HEADWORD: Shading
<hw>Shad"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Act or process of
making a shade.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That filling up which represents the effect of more
or less darkness, expressing rotundity, projection, etc., in a picture
or a drawing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shadoof</ent>⟦br⟧
